Set Up Email-to-Case

To efficiently resolve customer email inquiries, set up Email-to-Case to automatically create cases and auto-populate case fields from incoming emails. This feature is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience for Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Customize Application permission is needed to enable and set up Email-to-Case.

To set up Email-to-Case:

1. Turn On Email-to-Case
2. Configure Email-to-Case settings to customize case creation from incoming emails.
3. Add Routing Addresses for Email-to-Case to redirect case submissions to the email services address provided by Salesforce.

A case is created when the email address you specify is listed in the To, CC, or BCC fields of a customer email.
